1. Create repository
    Add a README file
    Add .gitignore
        .gitignore template: python
    Choose a license: MIT Licence

2. Click on Code and copy the path to clone the repository
3. Right click on windos folder where you need the project to be clonned and choose Open in Terminal
4. Enter the following command in terminal -  git clone paste the path copied from step 2
5. Enter into the folder using the cd command in terminal
6. Enter the command "code ." in terminal, so that it will open the VS code
